company_description:
Children’s feet grow quickly: on average a new shoe size is needed every ~4 months. That’s costly for families and wasteful for the planet. An even tougher problem is fit: every foot differs (length, width, height), yet the market still sells fixed sizes. It’s like one helmet size for every head—uncomfortable, unsafe, far from ideal. 95% of children are born with healthy feet; ~40% of adults develop problems, often linked to ill-fitting childhood shoes.
Sizeless fixes this. We build size-adjustable children’s shoes that grow with the foot. Our patent-pending mechanism lets parents dial in length and width across multiple sizes per pair—fewer pairs bought, less material waste, healthier foot development.
Our founding team met at adidas HQ. Sizeless began as a development project with On; we are now backed by Germany’s EXIST program and develop and source in Europe. Prototypes are being validated with the Institute for Biomechanics & Orthopaedics at the German Sport University Cologne.
